\dn3 Resource allocation
\b0 . When there are multiple users or multiple jobs running at the same time, resources must be allocated to each of them. The operating system manages many different types of resources. Some (such as 
\fs24 CPU 
\fs26\fsmilli13333 cycles, main memory, and file storage) may have special allocation code, whereas others (such as 
\fs24 I/O 
\fs26\fsmilli13333 devices) may have much more general request and release code. For instance, in determining how best to use the 
\fs24 CPU
\fs26\fsmilli13333 , operating systems have 
\fs24 CPU
\fs26\fsmilli13333 -scheduling routines that take into account the speed of the 
\fs24 CPU
\fs26\fsmilli13333 , the jobs that must be executed, the number of registers available, and other factors. 
